author: Justin Hawkins Rides Again
description:
First of all there's no bitterness here, but I am asking a genuine question, because I'm so confused. What does it take to make it on to a radio playlist and does it matter anyway? Let me know what you think. 

To watch Dancing With Echoes by Boyzlife: https://youtu.be/EeKr6KZ0U4E?si=UmBs7FR8Wfc1BSZX

Thank you to Soccer Six TV: https://youtu.be/gqpbxp9Q9WU?si=rVocaV2Eb5nuXcL4

The new Darkness album comes out next month,  you can pre-order 'Dreams On Toast' on CD, vinyl or cassette here: https://thedarkness.lnk.to/dreamsontoast/

See The Darkness on tour across the UK in March, tickets are on sale here: https://www.thedarknesslive.com/tour-dates/

From mid March, watch more episodes of Justin Hawkins Rides Again and find Behind The Scenes footage from The Darkness On Tour on my Patreon: http://www.patreon.com/jushawk

For Cameo messages: https://www.cameo.com/justinhawkins

title: Radio Playlists: Do They Matter?
